---
import MinimalLegalLayout from '../../layouts/MinimalLegalLayout.astro'
import { getBreadcrumbSchema } from '../../lib/seo'

const breadcrumbSchema = getBreadcrumbSchema([
  { name: 'Home', url: 'https://flexen.co/en/' },
  { name: 'Privacy Policy', url: 'https://flexen.co/en/privacy' },
])
---

<MinimalLegalLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Flexen UG"
  description="Privacy policy of Flexen UG (haftungsbeschränkt) for the website flexen.co and the Flexen app (iOS and Android)."
  locale="en"
  canonicalPath="/en/privacy"
  schema={breadcrumbSchema}
>
  <section class="section min-h-screen">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content max-w-3xl">
        <h1 class="font-heading text-h1 mb-4 font-bold">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="text-secondary text-body mb-12">
          This privacy policy applies to the website
          <strong class="text-white">flexen.co</strong> and to the
          <strong class="text-white">Flexen app</strong> (iOS and Android) by Flexen UG (haftungsbeschr&auml;nkt). It explains
          what data we process, for what purpose, on which legal basis — and what rights you have.
        </p>

        <div class="prose prose-invert text-secondary text-body space-y-8">
          <div>
            <h2 class="font-heading text-h3 mb-4 font-bold text-white">1. Controller</h2>
            <p>
              The controller for data processing on this website and in the Flexen app is:<br /><br />
              <strong class="text-white">Flexen UG (haftungsbeschr&auml;nkt)</strong><br />
              Paul-Heidelbach-Stra&szlig;e 14<br />
              34134 Kassel, Germany<br />
              Managing directors: Leonard Hoppe, Marcel Schneider, Leon Schmelzle<br />
              Commercial register: HRB 20498, Amtsgericht Kassel<br />
              Email: <a href="mailto:info@flexen.co" class="text-flexen-accent hover:underline">info@flexen.co</a>
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="font-heading text-h3 mb-4 font-bold text-white">2. Scope</h2>
            <p>This privacy policy covers two areas:</p>
            <ul class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
              <li>
                <strong class="text-white">Website</strong> (sections 3&ndash;5): visiting flexen.co and contacting us by
                email.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-white">Flexen app</strong> (sections 6&ndash;14): using the Flexen app for iOS and Android,
                including your account, health and nutrition data, AI features and purchases.
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-4">Sections 15&ndash;19 (recipients, retention, your rights) apply to both areas.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="font-heading text-h3 mb-4 font-bold text-white">3. Website: Hosting</h2>
            <p>
              This website is hosted by Google Firebase Hosting (Google Ireland Limited, Gordon House, Barrow Street,
              Dublin 4, Ireland). When you visit the website, information (e.g. IP address, time of access, page
              requested, user agent) is automatically stored in server log files. This data is used solely for the
              purpose of stable website operation and cannot be attributed to specific individuals. The legal basis is
              Art.&nbsp;6(1)(f) GDPR (legitimate interest in stable website operation).
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="font-heading text-h3 mb-4 font-bold text-white">4. Website: Contact by Email</h2>
            <p>
              When you contact us by email (e.g.
              <a href="mailto:info@flexen.co" class="text-flexen-accent hover:underline">info@flexen.co</a>), we process
              the data you submit (email address, content, name if provided) for the purpose of handling your request.
              Legal basis is Art.&nbsp;6(1)(f) GDPR (legitimate interest in responding). The data is deleted as soon as
              it is no longer required for our response and no statutory retention obligations apply.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="font-heading text-h3 mb-4 font-bold text-white">
              5. Website: No Cookies, No Tracking, Local Fonts
            </h2>
            <p>
              This website sets <strong class="text-white">no cookies</strong> and uses
              <strong class="text-white">no tracking</strong>. No third-party scripts (e.g. Google Analytics, Facebook
              Pixel) are embedded.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-4">
              This website uses locally hosted fonts (self-hosting). No connections to external font servers (e.g.
              Google Fonts) are established.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="font-heading text-h3 mb-4 font-bold text-white">6. Flexen App: Account &amp; Registration</h2>
            <p>Using the Flexen app requires an account. We offer the following sign-up and sign-in methods:</p>
            <ul class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
              <li>
                <strong class="text-white">Email and password</strong> — we send you a verification email to confirm your
                address.
              </li>
              <li><strong class="text-white">Google Sign-In</strong> — sign in with your Google account.</li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-white">Phone number</strong> — sign in via one-time code (SMS); your phone number is only
                stored when you use this method.
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-4">
              Authentication is handled by Firebase Authentication (Google). Your account is assigned a pseudonymous
              user ID (Firebase UID), which your app data is linked to.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-4">
              <strong class="text-white">Profile data:</strong> During onboarding and in your profile we process — to the
              extent you provide them — email address, username, display name, date of birth, height, weight, body fat percentage,
              gender, fitness goal, activity level, dietary preferences, allergies and intolerances, an optional note on pre-existing
              conditions, your medication status, your goals (calories, macros, water, steps) and your time zone.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-4">
              The Flexen app collects <strong class="text-white">no location data</strong>. No location permission is
              requested and no location is determined or stored.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-4">
              <strong class="text-white">Legal basis:</strong> Art.&nbsp;6(1)(b) GDPR (performance of the user contract).
              Where profile data constitutes health data (e.g. allergies, pre-existing conditions), section&nbsp;7 additionally
              applies.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="font-heading text-h3 mb-4 font-bold text-white">7. Flexen App: Health &amp; Nutrition Data</h2>
            <p>
              Flexen is an AI health coach. To make the app work, we process health data within the meaning of
              Art.&nbsp;9 GDPR — but only with your
              <strong class="text-white">explicit consent</strong> (Art.&nbsp;9(2)(a) GDPR), which you give during onboarding
              and can withdraw at any time with effect for the future (in the app settings or by email to
              <a href="mailto:info@flexen.co" class="text-flexen-accent hover:underline">info@flexen.co</a>).
            </p>
            <p class="mt-4">This includes — in each case only if you use the feature:</p>
            <ul class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
              <li>
                <strong class="text-white">Steps and sleep:</strong> With your permission, the app reads step count and sleep
                data from Apple HealthKit (iOS) or Android Health Connect. Sleep you log manually in Flexen can be written
                back to HealthKit/Health Connect. You control this access at any time via your device's system settings.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-white">Nutrition:</strong> meal logs, food photos, recipes and your fridge inventory.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-white">Medications:</strong> name, dosage, intake schedule and intake history. The AI
                accesses your medication data
                <strong class="text-white">only with a separate, additional consent</strong>, which you can give in the
                app and withdraw at any time.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-white">Journal &amp; mood:</strong> journal entries and your mood on a scale of 0&ndash;10.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-white">Cycle:</strong> if you use cycle tracking: start of your last period, cycle
                length and your contraceptive method (e.g. pill) to calculate your cycle phases.
              </li>
              <li><strong class="text-white">Weight &amp; water:</strong> weight history and water tracking.</li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-white">Training:</strong> AI-generated training plans and exercises.
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-4">
              All of this data is stored in Cloud Firestore or Cloud Storage (Google, processed in the europe-west1
              region) and linked to your Firebase UID.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-4">
              <strong class="text-white">Important:</strong> Flexen is not a medical device and does not replace medical advice,
              diagnosis or treatment.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="font-heading text-h3 mb-4 font-bold text-white">8. Flexen App: AI Features (Julio)</h2>
            <p>
              The AI coach <strong class="text-white">Julio</strong> and other AI features of the app use the Google Gemini
              AI model (Google Ireland Limited / Google LLC) via Firebase AI / Vertex AI. The following content is transmitted
              to Google:
            </p>
            <ul class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
              <li>
                <strong class="text-white">Chat messages</strong> you send to Julio, together with the profile context required
                to generate a response.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-white">Food photos</strong> for automatic nutrition analysis. Before upload, we strip
                the EXIF metadata (e.g. capture location, device info) from the image.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-white">Voice recordings</strong> (e.g. for journal entries) for transcription. The audio
                file is <strong class="text-white">not permanently stored</strong> — only the transcript is stored.
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-4">
              The AI accesses your medication data only with your separate consent (see section&nbsp;7).
            </p>
            <p class="mt-4">
              <strong class="text-white">Legal basis:</strong> Art.&nbsp;6(1)(b) GDPR (provision of the AI features as the
              core of the app); for health data, your explicit consent under Art.&nbsp;9(2)(a) GDPR.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-4">
              <strong class="text-white">Note:</strong> AI output can contain errors and is not medical advice. For health
              concerns, please consult a medical professional.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="font-heading text-h3 mb-4 font-bold text-white">
              9. Flexen App: Camera, Photo and Microphone Permissions
            </h2>
            <p>The app only requests device permissions when you use the corresponding feature:</p>
            <ul class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
              <li>
                <strong class="text-white">Camera:</strong> to photograph meals and scan barcodes.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-white">Photos/gallery:</strong> to select existing food photos.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-white">Microphone:</strong> for voice recordings that are transcribed (see section&nbsp;8).
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-white">Health data / activity recognition:</strong> to read steps and sleep (see section&nbsp;7).
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-white">Notifications:</strong> for reminders you configure in the app.
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-4">You can revoke any permission at any time in your device's system settings.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="font-heading text-h3 mb-4 font-bold text-white">
              10. Flexen App: External Food &amp; Medication Databases
            </h2>
            <p>
              To look up nutrition values and medications, the app queries external reference databases. Depending on the
              feature you use, only the respective search terms or barcode numbers are transmitted — not your profile:
            </p>
            <ul class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
              <li>
                <strong class="text-white">OpenFoodFacts</strong> (Open Food Facts, France) — When you scan a food
                barcode, only the product's <strong class="text-white">barcode number</strong> is transmitted — no
                personal data and no information from your account. Processing takes place in the EU; no third-country
                transfer.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-white">FatSecret Platform API</strong> (FatSecret, USA) — food and nutrition database.
                The request is routed through our server (Cloud Function in the EU, europe-west1 region); only the
                <strong class="text-white">food search term</strong> is passed to FatSecret, not your user ID. Where a
                transfer to the USA occurs, we rely on the EU Standard Contractual Clauses (Art.&nbsp;46(2)(c) GDPR).
                <!-- [NEEDS_LEGAL]: Verify FatSecret third-country safeguard (SCC/DPF certification) and an Art. 28 GDPR DPA before release. -->
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-white">USDA FoodData Central</strong> (U.S. Department of Agriculture, USA) —
                government food and nutrition database. The request is likewise routed through our server (Cloud Function
                in the EU); only the <strong class="text-white">food search term</strong> is transmitted, not your user ID.
                <!-- [NEEDS_LEGAL]: Clarify third-country legal basis for USDA (US authority, no standard DPF/DPA route). -->
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-white">NLM RxTerms / RxNav</strong> (U.S. National Library of Medicine, USA) —
                medication database for searching medication names. This request is made
                <strong class="text-white">directly from your device</strong> to a server in the USA. In doing so, the
                <strong class="text-white">medication search term</strong> you enter (a health-related data point) and your
                IP address are transmitted. A <strong class="text-white">third-country transfer to the USA</strong> takes
                place.
                <!-- [NEEDS_LEGAL]: Direct client call to clinicaltables.nlm.nih.gov in the USA. Art. 9 legal basis and third-country safeguard (US authority, no DPF/SCC available) unresolved; option: route the request through an EU proxy (Cloud Function) instead of directly from the client. Assess legally before release. -->
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-4">
              The legal basis for these lookup features is Art.&nbsp;6(1)(b) GDPR (provision of the respective feature);
              where medication search terms constitute health data, your explicit consent under Art.&nbsp;9(2)(a) GDPR.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="font-heading text-h3 mb-4 font-bold text-white">11. Flexen App: Purchases</h2>
            <p>
              Subscriptions and one-time purchases (Flexen Monthly, Flexen Yearly with a 7-day trial, Flexen Lifetime)
              are handled entirely by the Apple App Store or Google Play. Payment processing is carried out exclusively
              by Apple or Google — we receive
              <strong class="text-white">no payment data</strong> (no credit card or bank details), only the information about
              your subscription status. Legal basis is Art.&nbsp;6(1)(b) GDPR (performance of contract). The privacy policies
              of Apple and Google apply to their data processing.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="font-heading text-h3 mb-4 font-bold text-white">12. Flexen App: Crash Reports (Crashlytics)</h2>
            <p>
              To detect and fix app crashes, we use Firebase Crashlytics (Google). This processes diagnostic data (e.g.
              time of crash, device model, OS version, app version, stack trace). We do not enrich crash reports with
              personal content. Legal basis is Art.&nbsp;6(1)(f) GDPR (legitimate interest in a stable, error-free app).
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="font-heading text-h3 mb-4 font-bold text-white">13. Flexen App: Analytics (PostHog)</h2>
            <p>
              <strong class="text-white">Currently, no usage analytics are active in the Flexen app.</strong>
              No analytics data leaves your device.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-4">
              Should we activate usage analytics in the future, the following applies: we will use
              <strong class="text-white">PostHog</strong> (PostHog Inc., 2261 Market Street #4008, San Francisco, CA 94114,
              USA) — exclusively with your explicit consent and with data processing on EU servers in Frankfurt, Germany.
              Where third-country transfers or access from the USA occur, we rely on appropriate safeguards, in particular
              the EU-US Data Privacy Framework and EU Standard Contractual Clauses.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-4">
              <strong class="text-white">Legal basis:</strong> Art.&nbsp;6(1)(a) GDPR (consent). The feature is
              <strong class="text-white">disabled by default</strong> (opt-in) and can be enabled or withdrawn at any time
              in the app settings under &ldquo;Anonymous usage statistics&rdquo;.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-4">
              <strong class="text-white">Purpose (if activated):</strong> improving the app, detecting errors, understanding
              which features are used, measuring user retention.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-4"><strong class="text-white">Data processed (if activated):</strong></p>
            <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
              <li>
                Event metadata (e.g. &ldquo;meal logged&rdquo;, &ldquo;workout completed&rdquo;),
                <strong class="text-white">without</strong> meal or workout content
              </li>
              <li>Screen views and tab switches</li>
              <li>Device and operating system information (model, OS version, language)</li>
              <li>A pseudonymous user ID (Firebase UID) to associate events</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-4">
              <strong class="text-white">What we explicitly do NOT collect:</strong> the contents of your meals, chat messages
              with Julio, weight values, steps, sleep data or any other health parameters.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-4">
              <strong class="text-white">Data processing agreement:</strong> Before activation, we will enter into a Data
              Processing Agreement (DPA) with PostHog pursuant to Art.&nbsp;28 GDPR. PostHog privacy policy: <a
                href="https://posthog.com/privacy"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                class="text-flexen-accent hover:underline">posthog.com/privacy</a
              >.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="font-heading text-h3 mb-4 font-bold text-white">14. Flexen App: Friends Feature</h2>
            <p>
              The friends feature is <strong class="text-white">opt-in</strong>: it only becomes active when you send or
              accept a friend request. Confirmed friends see an activity snapshot of you: streak, daily steps, daily
              calories, water, mood index, workout status and when you were last active. Detailed data (e.g. individual
              meals, journal entries, medications) is
              <strong class="text-white">not</strong> shared.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-4">
              <strong class="text-white">Legal basis:</strong> your consent (Art.&nbsp;6(1)(a) GDPR; for the health values
              included, Art.&nbsp;9(2)(a) GDPR). You can end friendships at any time — sharing of your activity data ends
              with them.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="font-heading text-h3 mb-4 font-bold text-white">15. Recipients &amp; Third-Country Transfers</h2>
            <p>We use the following service providers (processors or independent controllers):</p>
            <ul class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
              <li>
                <strong class="text-white">Google Ireland Limited / Google LLC</strong> — Firebase Authentication, Cloud Firestore,
                Cloud Storage, Cloud Functions (europe-west1 region), Firebase AppCheck, Crashlytics and Firebase AI / Vertex
                AI (Gemini) for the AI features.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-white">OpenFoodFacts</strong> (France) — product data for barcode scans (barcode number
                only, see section&nbsp;10).
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-white">FatSecret</strong> (USA) and <strong class="text-white">USDA FoodData Central</strong>
                (USA) — food/nutrition databases, each via our server proxy in the EU and with the search term only (see
                section&nbsp;10).
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-white">U.S. National Library of Medicine (NLM RxTerms / RxNav)</strong> (USA) —
                medication search; queried directly from your device to the USA with the search term and IP address (see
                section&nbsp;10).
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-white">Apple / Google</strong> — handling of purchases and subscriptions (see section&nbsp;11).
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-white">PostHog Inc.</strong> — only if usage analytics are activated (see section&nbsp;13).
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-4">
              Processing primarily takes place in the EU (europe-west1 region). Where Google services transfer data to
              the USA, the transfer is based on the EU Standard Contractual Clauses (Art.&nbsp;46(2)(c) GDPR) and on the
              EU-US Data Privacy Framework, under which Google is certified (as of 12 June 2026). We have a Data
              Processing Agreement with Google pursuant to Art.&nbsp;28 GDPR.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-4">
              For the food and medication databases named in section&nbsp;10 (FatSecret, USDA FoodData Central, NLM
              RxTerms / RxNav), data may be transferred to the USA. For the medication search via the NLM (US authority),
              the request is made directly from your device.
              <!-- [NEEDS_LEGAL]: Verify third-country safeguards for FatSecret/USDA/NLM (SCC, DPF certification or Art. 49 GDPR derogation) and Art. 28 GDPR DPAs; consider an EU proxy solution for the direct NLM client call. -->
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="font-heading text-h3 mb-4 font-bold text-white">16. Retention &amp; Deletion</h2>
            <p>
              We store your app data for as long as your account exists. When you delete your account, your personal
              data is deleted or anonymised in our active systems unless statutory retention obligations require longer
              storage. This includes profile, meal and daily logs, journal entries, AI chats, training plans,
              medications, cycle data, recipes, fridge inventory, weight history, achievements, weekly summaries,
              activity logs and snapshots, friendship data (on both sides), data exports, uploaded
              images and your sign-in account. Backups are overwritten within 30 days at the latest.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-4">How to delete your account:</p>
            <ul class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
              <li>
                <strong class="text-white">In the app:</strong> Settings &rarr; Account &rarr; &ldquo;Delete account&rdquo;
                (with confirmation dialog) — deletion is started immediately.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-white">By email:</strong> to
                <a href="mailto:info@flexen.co" class="text-flexen-accent hover:underline">info@flexen.co</a> — we delete
                your account within 30 days.
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-4">
              A step-by-step guide is available at
              <a href="/en/delete-account" class="text-flexen-accent hover:underline">flexen.co/en/delete-account</a>.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="font-heading text-h3 mb-4 font-bold text-white">17. Your Rights</h2>
            <p>You have the right to:</p>
            <ul class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
              <li>Access your stored data (Art.&nbsp;15 GDPR)</li>
              <li>Rectification of inaccurate data (Art.&nbsp;16 GDPR)</li>
              <li>Erasure of your data (Art.&nbsp;17 GDPR)</li>
              <li>Restriction of processing (Art.&nbsp;18 GDPR)</li>
              <li>Data portability (Art.&nbsp;20 GDPR)</li>
              <li>Object to processing (Art.&nbsp;21 GDPR)</li>
              <li>
                Lodge a complaint with a data protection authority (Art.&nbsp;77 GDPR), in particular the
                <a
                  href="https://datenschutz.hessen.de/"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener"
                  class="text-flexen-accent hover:underline"
                  >Hessian Commissioner for Data Protection and Freedom of Information</a
                >
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-4">
              You can withdraw any consent you have given (e.g. for health data or AI access to your medication data) at
              any time with effect for the future (Art.&nbsp;7(3) GDPR).
            </p>
            <p class="mt-4">
              Contact us at: <a href="mailto:info@flexen.co" class="text-flexen-accent hover:underline"
                >info@flexen.co</a
              >
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="font-heading text-h3 mb-4 font-bold text-white">18. External Links</h2>
            <p>
              This website links to the Apple App Store and Google Play Store. The respective privacy policies of Apple
              and Google apply to data processing by these services.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2 class="font-heading text-h3 mb-4 font-bold text-white">19. Changes</h2>
            <p>
              We reserve the right to update this privacy policy to reflect changes in the legal landscape or in our
              services. The current version is always available on this page.<br /><br />
              Last updated: 12 June 2026 (version 2.0)
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</MinimalLegalLayout>
